esent a simple strategy with idle time $3\\Lambda_{2k}$ that splits the unit\nline into not-disjoint $k$ segments of equal length that robots synchronously\ncover. Then, we present a complex strategy that split the unit line into $k$\nnon-disjoint segments that robots asynchronously cover.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Oct 2019 23:20:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-04"}
