 with gluino and/or stop for\n$m_{\\tilde{g}},m_{\\tilde{t}}\\approx m_{\\tilde{\\chi}_{1}^{0}} \\in [0.9-1.5]$\nTeV. The 100 TeV FCC collider can probe the gluino masses up to about 6 TeV\nwith $36.1~fb^{-1}$ integrated luminosity. We also find that the decay\n$\\tilde{g}\\rightarrow \\tilde{t}t$ can indirectly probe the stop mass up to\nabout 4 TeV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Oct 2019 13:29:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-04"}
